        },
        {
          "block_id": "p7_b6",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Kospi PBR Near 2 Times... Entering a Phase of Selective\nInvestment After Undervaluation Eases",
          "bbox": [
            0.223947,
            0.602993,
            0.560512,
            0.03502
          ],
          "reading_order": 6
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p7_b7",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "There is analysis that the structural undervaluation of the Korean stock market has\nbeen largely resolved, as the price-to-book ratio (PBR) of the domestic market has\napproached 2 times. Since the beginning of this month, domestic demand sectors\nsuch as banking, retail, insurance, and construction have shown a stronger trend\nthan semiconductors. This is evaluated as a reflection in share prices of expectations\nfor shareholder-return policies, as the perception of undervaluation has combined\nwith expectations for amendments to the Commercial Act. In the past as well, a\nKospi PBR of 2 times was reached only during limited periods, so the current level\nis interpreted as a meaningful range.",
          "bbox": [
            0.223948,
            0.655222,
            0.569334,
            0.127114
          ],
          "reading_order": 7
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p7_b8",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "However, as the valuation of domestic demand sectors has been normalized to some\nextent, experts advise that going forward, investors need a selective strategy that\nconsiders profitability in addition to simply targeting low PBR.",
          "bbox": [
            0.223948,
            0.797747,
            0.568163,
            0.041602
          ],
          "reading_order": 8
        },
