          "reading_order": 3
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p10_b4",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Once known as one of the youngest female\nbillionaires in South Korea and deemed an\ninfluential figure in the airline industry, Ms\nCho, also known as Heather Cho, is now\nmore likely to be called \"nut- rage woman\"\ninstead.",
          "bbox": [
            0.485992,
            0.203252,
            0.324161,
            0.092912
          ],
          "reading_order": 4
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p10_b5",
          "block_type": "figure",
          "text": "",
          "bbox": [
            0.202782,
            0.208808,
            0.277162,
            0.224487
          ],
          "reading_order": 5
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p10_b6",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "The label has stuck since the former\nexecutive vice-president notoriously\nordered a taxiing Korean Air flight to turn\nback at New York's John F. Kennedy\nInternational Airport last December to eject\ntwo cabin crew members for serving her\nmacadamia nuts in a bag instead of on a\nplate.",
          "bbox": [
